{"parse":{"title":"Ink brush","pageid":581819,"revid":854556800,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:CMOC_Treasures_of_Ancient_China_exhibit_-_calligraphy_brush_with_dragon_design.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6f/CMOC_Treasures_of_Ancient_China_exhibit_-_calligraphy_brush_with_dragon_design.jpg/220px-CMOC_Treasures_of_Ancient_China_exhibit_-_calligraphy_brush_with_dragon_design.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"132\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6f/CMOC_Treasures_of_Ancient_China_exhibit_-_calligraphy_brush_with_dragon_design.jpg/330px-CMOC_Treasures_of_Ancient_China_exhibit_-_calligraphy_brush_with_dragon_design.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6f/CMOC_Treasures_of_Ancient_China_exhibit_-_calligraphy_brush_with_dragon_design.jpg/440px-CMOC_Treasures_of_Ancient_China_exhibit_-_calligraphy_brush_with_dragon_design.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"2760\" data-file-height=\"1656\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:CMOC_Treasures_of_Ancient_China_exhibit_-_calligraphy_brush_with_dragon_design.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Ink brush with golden dragon design, used by the <a href=\"/wiki/Wanli_Emperor\" title=\"Wanli Emperor\">Wanli Emperor</a> (1563-1620).</div></div></div>\n<p><b>Ink brushes</b> (<a href=\"/wiki/Simplified_Chinese_characters\" title=\"Simplified Chinese characters\">simplified Chinese</a>&#58; <span lang=\"zh-Hans\">\u6bdb\u7b14</span>; <a href=\"/wiki/Traditional_Chinese_characters\" title=\"Traditional Chinese characters\">traditional Chinese</a>&#58; <span lang=\"zh-Hant\">\u6bdb\u7b46</span>; <a href=\"/wiki/Pinyin\" title=\"Pinyin\">pinyin</a>&#58; <i><span lang=\"zh-Latn-pinyin\">m\u00e1o b\u01d0</span></i>; <a href=\"/wiki/Japanese_language\" title=\"Japanese language\">Japanese</a>: <span lang=\"ja\">\u7b46</span>, <small><a href=\"/wiki/Romanization_of_Japanese\" title=\"Romanization of Japanese\">translit.</a>&#160;</small><i lang=\"ja-Latn\" title=\"Japanese-language transliteration\">fude</i>; <a href=\"/wiki/Korean_language\" title=\"Korean language\">Korean</a>: <span lang=\"ko\">\ubd93/\u7b46</span>) are used in <a href=\"/wiki/Chinese_calligraphy\" title=\"Chinese calligraphy\">Chinese calligraphy</a> as well as <a href=\"/wiki/Japanese_calligraphy\" title=\"Japanese calligraphy\">Japanese calligraphy</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Korean_calligraphy\" title=\"Korean calligraphy\">Korean calligraphy</a> which have a root of Chinese calligraphy. They are also used in <a href=\"/wiki/Chinese_painting\" title=\"Chinese painting\">Chinese painting</a> and other <a href=\"/wiki/Brush_painting\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Brush painting\">brush painting</a> styles. The brush was invented in China around 300 B.C.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> Together with the <a href=\"/wiki/Inkstone\" title=\"Inkstone\">inkstone</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Inkstick\" title=\"Inkstick\">inkstick</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Xuan_paper\" title=\"Xuan paper\">Xuan paper</a>, these four writing implements form the <a href=\"/wiki/Four_Treasures_of_the_Study\" title=\"Four Treasures of the Study\">Four Treasures of the Study</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Types\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Types</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Fudepen\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Fudepen</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#See_also\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Types\">Types</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Ink_brush&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Types\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:172px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Upper_Lascar_Row,_Hong_Kong_(2051987459).jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/16/Upper_Lascar_Row%2C_Hong_Kong_%282051987459%29.jpg/170px-Upper_Lascar_Row%2C_Hong_Kong_%282051987459%29.jpg\" width=\"170\" height=\"235\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/16/Upper_Lascar_Row%2C_Hong_Kong_%282051987459%29.jpg/255px-Upper_Lascar_Row%2C_Hong_Kong_%282051987459%29.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/16/Upper_Lascar_Row%2C_Hong_Kong_%282051987459%29.jpg/340px-Upper_Lascar_Row%2C_Hong_Kong_%282051987459%29.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"2221\" data-file-height=\"3071\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Upper_Lascar_Row,_Hong_Kong_(2051987459).jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Ink brushes of various size and material for sale</div></div></div>\n<p>Brushes differ greatly in terms of size, texture, material, and cost. The brush hair chosen depends on one's needs at the moment; certain kinds of brushes are more suited to certain <a href=\"/wiki/East_asian_script_styles\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"East asian script styles\">script styles </a> and individuals than others. \n</p>\n<ul><li><b>Handle</b>: usually of bamboo, exotic brushes may instead use such materials as gold, silver, jade, ivory, <a href=\"/wiki/Red_sandalwood\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Red sandalwood\">red sandalwood</a> or <a href=\"/wiki/Spotted_bamboo\" title=\"Spotted bamboo\">spotted bamboo</a>.</li>\n<li><b>Hair source</b>: normally the brush is made from goat, <a href=\"/wiki/Siberian_weasel\" title=\"Siberian weasel\">Siberian weasel</a> (ch: \u9ec4\u9f20\u72fc hu\u00e1ngsh\u01d4l\u00e1ng, yellow-rat-wolf), pig, mouse, <a href=\"/wiki/Domestic_buffalo\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Domestic buffalo\">buffalo</a>, wolf, or rabbit hair, while exotic ones can be made from tiger, <a href=\"/wiki/Fowl\" title=\"Fowl\">fowl</a>, deer, and even human hair (from a baby's first haircut, said to bring good fortune while taking the <a href=\"/wiki/Imperial_examination\" title=\"Imperial examination\">imperial examinations</a>).</li>\n<li><b>Hair texture</b>: soft (ch: \u8edf\u6beb ru\u01cenh\u00e1o), mixed (ch: \u517c\u6beb ji\u0101nh\u00e1o), or hard (ch: \u786c\u6beb y\u00ecngh\u00e1o) hair.</li>\n<li><b>Hair size</b>: generally classified as either big (ch: \u5927\u6977 d\u00e0k\u01cei, ja: \u5927\u7b46 oofude), medium (ch: \u4e2d\u6977 zh\u014dngk\u01cei, ja: \u4e2d\u7b46 chufude), or small (ch: \u5c0f\u6977 xi\u01ceok\u01cei, ja: \u5c0f\u7b46 kofude)<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>; most calligraphy is written with a medium-sized brush. The smallest brushes are used for very small pieces and for fashioning designs for seals. While medium size brushes are the most widely used, wielded by a skilled artist a medium brush can produce a variety of thicknesses of line from very thin to fairly thick. The largest brushes are used only for very large pieces.</li>\n<li><b>Hair length</b>: generally classified by hair length for thickness of handle as either long (ja: \u9577\u92d2 chouhou), medium (ja: \u4e2d\u92d2 chuhou), short (ja: \u77ed\u92d2\u3000tannhou); most calligraphy is written with a medium-length hair brush. The long hair brush are more keep to hold a ink than the short hair brushes as their length. So, it used for continuous long stroke line scripting such as Japanese traditional <i>hiragana</i> style by <i>rennmen</i>( ja: \u9023\u7dbf ). The hair of long hair brushes are tend to made by hard texture hair to keep their hair form, but there is a not one. Japanese very long and slender hair brushes called <i>menso</i>-burushes\uff08 ja: \u9762\u76f8\u7b46 \uff09 are used for detail painting.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup></li></ul>\n<p>Synthetic hair is not traditionally used. Prices vary greatly depending on the quality of the brush; cheap brushes cost less than one US dollar while expensive brushes can cost more than a thousand dollars. Currently, the finest brushes are made in the town of <a href=\"/wiki/Shanlian\" title=\"Shanlian\">Shanlian</a>, in the <a href=\"/wiki/Nanxun_District\" title=\"Nanxun District\">Nanxun District</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Prefecture-level_city\" title=\"Prefecture-level city\">prefecture-level city</a> of <a href=\"/wiki/Huzhou\" title=\"Huzhou\">Huzhou</a>, of <a href=\"/wiki/Zhejiang\" title=\"Zhejiang\">Zhejiang</a> province.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Ink_brush&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: History\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Pinceaux_chinois.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Pinceaux_chinois.jpg/220px-Pinceaux_chinois.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"123\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Pinceaux_chinois.jpg/330px-Pinceaux_chinois.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Pinceaux_chinois.jpg/440px-Pinceaux_chinois.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"1952\" data-file-height=\"1094\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Pinceaux_chinois.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Brushes of various sizes and types of hair, including one of chicken feathers at the top</div></div></div>\n<table class=\"plainlinks metadata ambox mbox-small-left ambox-content\" role=\"presentation\"><tbody><tr><td class=\"mbox-image\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Wiki_letter_w_cropped.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"[icon]\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1c/Wiki_letter_w_cropped.svg/20px-Wiki_letter_w_cropped.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"14\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1c/Wiki_letter_w_cropped.svg/30px-Wiki_letter_w_cropped.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1c/Wiki_letter_w_cropped.svg/40px-Wiki_letter_w_cropped.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"44\" data-file-height=\"31\" /></a></td><td class=\"mbox-text\"><div class=\"mbox-text-span\">This section <b>needs expansion</b>. <small>You can help by <a class=\"external text\" href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Ink_brush&amp;action=edit&amp;section=\">adding to it</a>.</small>  <small><i>(June 2008)</i></small></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p>The earliest intact ink brush was found in 1954 in the tomb of a <a href=\"/wiki/Chu_(state)\" title=\"Chu (state)\">Chu</a> citizen from the <a href=\"/wiki/Warring_States_period\" title=\"Warring States period\">Warring States period</a> (475-221 <a href=\"/wiki/Common_Era\" title=\"Common Era\">BCE</a>) located in an archaeological dig site <i>Zuo Gong Shan 15</i> near <a href=\"/wiki/Changsha\" title=\"Changsha\">Changsha</a> (\u9577\u6c99). The primitive version of an ink brush found had a wooden stalk and a bamboo tube securing the bundle of hair to the stalk. Legend wrongly credits the invention of the ink brush to the later <a href=\"/wiki/Qin_dynasty\" title=\"Qin dynasty\">Qin</a> general <a href=\"/wiki/Meng_Tian\" title=\"Meng Tian\">Meng Tian</a>.<sup class=\"noprint Inline-Template Template-Fact\" style=\"white-space:nowrap;\">&#91;<i><a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed\" title=\"Wikipedia:Citation needed\"><span title=\"This claim needs references to reliable sources. (May 2015)\">citation needed</span></a></i>&#93;</sup>\n</p><p>Traces of the writing brush, however, were discovered on the Shang jades, and were suggested to be the grounds of the oracle bone inscriptions.<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Fudepen\">Fudepen</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Ink_brush&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Fudepen\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\">See also: <a href=\"/wiki/Fudepen\" title=\"Fudepen\">Fudepen</a></div>\n<p>The <b>Fudepen</b>, also known as a \"Brush Pen\", is a modern Japanese invention analogous to a <a href=\"/wiki/Fountain_pen\" title=\"Fountain pen\">Fountain pen</a>. Today, Japanese companies such as <a href=\"/wiki/Pentel\" title=\"Pentel\">Pentel</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Sakura_Color_Products_Corporation\" title=\"Sakura Color Products Corporation\">Sakura Color Products Corporation</a> manufacture pens with tips resembling those of a small ink brush. These brush pens work almost identically to small ink brushes and can be used for most of the same purposes.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Ink_brush&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Chinese_calligraphy\" title=\"Chinese calligraphy\">Chinese calligraphy</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Huzhou_ink_brush\" title=\"Huzhou ink brush\">Huzhou ink brush</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Japanese_calligraphy\" title=\"Japanese calligraphy\">Japanese calligraphy</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Korean_calligraphy\" title=\"Korean calligraphy\">Korean calligraphy</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Xuan_writing_brush\" title=\"Xuan writing brush\">Xuan writing brush</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Ink_brush&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<table role=\"presentation\" class=\"mbox-small plainlinks sistersitebox\" style=\"background-color:#f9f9f9;border:1px solid #aaa;color:#000\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<td class=\"mbox-image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/4a/Commons-logo.svg/30px-Commons-logo.svg.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"40\" class=\"noviewer\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/4a/Commons-logo.svg/45px-Commons-logo.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/4a/Commons-logo.svg/59px-Commons-logo.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"1024\" data-file-height=\"1376\" /></td>\n<td class=\"mbox-text plainlist\">Wikimedia Commons has media related to <i><b><a href=\"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Category:Ink_brushes\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"commons:Category:Ink brushes\">Ink brushes</a></b></i>.</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Ong, Siew Chey (2005). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=bt7q8hfiZ4gC\"><i>China condensed: 5000 years of history &amp; culture</i></a>. Singapore: Marshall Cavendish. p.&#160;161. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-981-261-067-6\" title=\"Special:BookSources/978-981-261-067-6\">978-981-261-067-6</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=China+condensed%3A+5000+years+of+history+%26+culture&amp;rft.place=Singapore&amp;rft.pages=161&amp;rft.pub=Marshall+Cavendish&amp;rft.date=2005&amp;rft.isbn=978-981-261-067-6&amp;rft.aulast=Ong&amp;rft.aufirst=Siew+Chey&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3Dbt7q8hfiZ4gC&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AInk+brush\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=nJWyAAAAIAAJ\"><i>Women of China, Issues 1-6</i></a>. Foreign Language Press. 1995. p.&#160;1.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Women+of+China%2C+Issues+1-6&amp;rft.pages=1&amp;rft.pub=Foreign+Language+Press&amp;rft.date=1995&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks